                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/136</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-04T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>339. Foreign Minister tells me that there is no doubt about the ratification of
                    the treaty in November. Three parties have agreed to support it; but it will
                    increase the majority if the United States Senate ratifies the treaty as soon as
                    possible. This I look upon as most desirable. A delay may produce other delays
                    here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
